cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "closure: an open research program on inference-time structure in LLMs"
message: "If you use or refer to this program, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Ryzhkov"
    given-names: "Vlad"
    alias: "data-mission"
repository-code: "https://github.com/data-mission/closure"
url: "https://github.com/data-mission/closure"
abstract: >-
  An open research program investigating whether language-model inference
  can be described, and eventually programmed, through structural
  properties — constraint, dependency, perturbation, release, coupling,
  stabilization — while treating language as a lossy observable rather
  than assuming it is the model's native computational ontology. The
  founding ontology is reduced to eight falsifiable experiments, each
  with pre-registered verdict conditions and a kill condition, a living
  hypothesis registry, and a citation-verification ledger. Originated and
  led by Vlad Ryzhkov.
keywords:
  - large language models
  - interpretability
  - mechanistic interpretability
  - hallucination
  - uncertainty quantification
  - llm evaluation
  - factor analysis
  - pre-registration
  - open science
license: MIT
version: "0.1.0"
